profiles_PCAWG = pd.read_csv ("./Data/WGS_PCAWG.96.csv")
target_index = [sid.split('::')[0] == "ColoRect-AdenoCA" for sid in list(profiles_PCAWG.columns[2:])]
crc_PCAWG = profiles_PCAWG.iloc[:,2:].loc[:, target_index]
crc_PCAWG.columns = [sid.split('::')[1] for sid in crc_PCAWG.columns.values]

POLE_samples = pd.read_csv("./Data/CRC_POLE.samples")
pole = {i.split("..")[1]:1 for i in POLE_samples['CRC.POLE']}

MSI_samples = pd.read_csv("./Data/CRC_MSI.samples")
msi = {i.split("..")[1]:1 for i in MSI_samples['CRC.MSI']}

new_names = crc_PCAWG.columns.values.copy()
for i in range(len(new_names)):
    if msi.get(new_names[i], 0) == 1:
        new_names[i] = new_names[i] + "_MSI"
    elif pole.get (new_names[i], 0) == 1:
        new_names[i] = new_names[i] + "_POLE"        
    else:
        new_names[i] = new_names[i] + "_MSS"
        
crc_PCAWG.columns = new_names

crc_PCAWG_norm = crc_PCAWG/crc_PCAWG.sum()
sim_96c = cosine_similarity(crc_PCAWG_norm.values.T, crc_PCAWG_norm.values.T)

plt.figure(figsize=(13,13))
sns.set(font_scale=0.8)

                       xticklabels = crc_PCAWG_norm.columns.values,

                   cbar_kws = {'shrink': .6,  'aspect':8,'ticks' : np.linspace(0, 1,5),

## figure setting
fig, (ax1, ax2, ax3) = plt.subplots(1,3, figsize=(4,1.6), sharey = True)
sns.set(style="whitegrid", color_codes=True, rc={"grid.linewidth": 0.5, 'grid.color': '.7', 
                                                 'ytick.major.size': 2,
                                                 'axes.edgecolor': '.3', 
                                                 'axes.linewidth': 1.35,})
customPalette = sns.set_palette(sns.color_palette(['orange', 'silver']))

for ax,target in zip([ax1, ax2, ax3],['POLE', 'MSS', 'MSI']):
    
    group, label, sim = [], [], []

    df_tmp1 = crc_PCAWG_norm_80c.loc[:, ## within group data
                                 [sample.split ("_")[1] == target for sample in crc_PCAWG_norm_80c.columns]].copy()
    
    sim_tmp1 = cosine_similarity(df_tmp1.values.T, df_tmp1.values.T) ## cosine similarities within the group
    tri_sim1 = sim_tmp1[np.triu_indices(len(sim_tmp1), k = 1)] ## take the triangle values, diagonal not included
    
    print (f'Mean of pair-wise similarity of {target}-CRCs: {np.mean (tri_sim1):.2f}') ## mean of the values
    
    df_tmp2 = crc_PCAWG_norm_80c.loc[:, ## out-group data
                                 [sample.split ("_")[1] != target for sample in crc_PCAWG_norm_80c.columns]].copy()
   
    sim_tmp2 = cosine_similarity(df_tmp1.values.T, df_tmp2.values.T) ## cosine similarities with the outgroup
    a, b = sim_tmp2.shape
    tri_sim2 = sim_tmp2.reshape(a * b)
    
    t, p = mannwhitneyu(tri_sim1, tri_sim2, alternative='two-sided') ## difference test
    
    ## making data frame for the target group:
    sim += list(tri_sim1) + list (tri_sim2)
    label += ['Within group'] * len(tri_sim1) + ['Between group'] * len(tri_sim2)
    group += [target] * (len(tri_sim1) + len(tri_sim2))
    sim_df = pd.DataFrame({"Group": group, "label": label,"Pair-wise_simlarities": sim})
    
    ## plot the results
    sns.violinplot(x = 'Group', y = "Pair-wise_simlarities", hue = label, data = sim_df, ax = ax, palette= customPalette)
    
    ## adding p value on the plot     
    x1, x2 = -0.20, 0.20
    y, h, col = sim_df['Pair-wise_simlarities'].max()+0.1, 0.1, 'black'
    ax.plot([x1, x1, x2, x2], [y, y+h, y+h, y], lw=0.5, c = col)
    ax.text((x1+x2)*.5, y + h + 0.1, 'p : {0:1.1e}'.format(p), ha='center', va='bottom', color=col)
    
    sns.despine()
    ax.grid (linestyle='-', linewidth=0.3)
    ax.set_xlabel("")
    
    if target == "POLE": 
        ax.set_ylabel("CRC sample pair\ncosine similarity(80channel)", size = 11, color = "black")
    else:
        ax.set_ylabel("")
        
    if target == "MSI": 
        ax.legend ( bbox_to_anchor=(1, -0.17), frameon = False, fontsize=11, ncol = 2)
    else:
        ax.legend ('', frameon = False)    
    
    for tick in ax.xaxis.get_major_ticks():
        tick.label.set_fontsize(11)
    
plt.subplots_adjust(wspace=0, hspace=0)
plt.show()

Mean of pair-wise similarity of POLE-CRCs: 0.96
Mean of pair-wise similarity of MSS-CRCs: 0.90
Mean of pair-wise similarity of MSI-CRCs: 0.93

df_reconstructed = pd.DataFrame()
df_reconstructed['53C_Concordant'] = FFPE_profiles['53C_Concordant'][reverse_T2C_ind].copy()

for i, sample in enumerate(original_profiles.columns[1:5]):
    if "unrepaired" in sample:
        reconstructed_tmp, corrected_profiles_df = correct_FFPE_profile(v = original_profiles[sample].to_numpy(), 
                                                                        w1 = ffpe_sig_unrepaired,
                                                                        sample_id = sample)
    else:
        reconstructed_tmp, corrected_profiles_df = correct_FFPE_profile(v = original_profiles[sample].to_numpy(), 
                                                                        w1 = ffpe_sig_repaired,
                                                                        sample_id = sample)
          
    df_reconstructed[sample + '_Corrected'] = reconstructed_tmp[reverse_T2C_ind].copy()
    
    if i == 1: ## add data to prepare the plot later
        df_reconstructed[''] = [0] * sum(reverse_T2C_ind)
        df_reconstructed['C277_Concordant'] = FFPE_profiles['C277_Concordant'][reverse_T2C_ind].copy()

labels_pal = [sns.color_palette("Set2")[0],'grey',sns.color_palette("Set2")[2]]

length = len(labels)
labels_colors = {label:labels_pal[i] for i,label in enumerate(labels)}

for i in range(length):
    ## bottom pannel color bars 
    left, width = sum(sample_num[:i])/len(individual_lables) + 0.001, sample_num[i]/len(individual_lables) - 0.005
        
    bottom, height = 1.05, 0.13
    right = left + width
    top = bottom + height
    ax = plt.gca()
    col = labels_colors[labels[i]]
    p = plt.Rectangle((left, bottom), width, height, fill=True, color = col)
    p.set_transform(ax.transAxes)
    p.set_clip_on(False)
    ax.add_patch(p)
    
    ax.text(0.5 * (left + right), 0.5 * (bottom + top), labels[i], color = "white", size = 13,weight = "bold",
